JOHANNESBURG - South Africa’s unemployment rate has increased in the second quarter of the year. The country’s unemployment rate is now 27.2 percent. StatsSA's quarterly labour force survey says unemployment increased due to 102,000 job losses. Unemployment amongst the youth continue to increase and is now nearly 54 percent. The biggest employment losses were recorded in manufacturing, services and trade industries. StatsSA says Black Africans and Coloureds remains the most vulnerable in the job market. eNCA